title: For Sale:  New
postcontent: This is a Swiss Arms Neuhausen (SAN) P210-5LS longslide heavy frame pistol in 9mm Para, serial number P330766, one of only 200 made as the final Swiss designed and manufactured P210 variant. Based on the lack of cycling wear on the rails and on top of the barrel, and the lack of erosion on the breech face, the pistol appears to be unfired ex-factory. It is all original as shipped by Swiss Arms, except for the extra factory magazine that I added to replace the missing spare. The long slide unique to this model is fitted with factory micrometer adjustable sights. The late pattern heavy frame features the final factory modification comprising a lateral magazine catch and an extended and raised tang complemented by a hammer with its tang slightly rounded in the lower rear corner. The original factory matte blue finish rates better than 99%, with no discernible wear other than a hint of an “idiot scratch” visible only in the right light ahead of the slide stop, and slight finish loss around the magwell and on the magazine. The action operates correctly and exceptionally smoothly in cycling and lockup. All numbers match on the frame, slide, and barrel. The pistol bears 2004 German Ulm nitro proofs date coded AE. The slide is marked by a Jaspo logo in a rectangle; Simpson Ltd importer marks are laser engraved on the butt above the magwell in lieu of the ugly SIGARMS logo missing from the slide. The numbered factory box also contains a correct spare magazine, a factory magazine loader, a factory test target dated 6 December 2004 showing five shots going into a vertical string measuring 44x14mm, a German retailer tag from Eduard Kettner of Cologne, a correct late white cover Swiss Arms factory manual, a 2004 Swiss Arms mini-folder, and an unmarked and unused ERLA Swiss centerfire cleaning kit.
